'''''Jedi Quest: The School of Fear''''' is the fifth in a [[Star Wars: Jedi Quest (novel series)|series]] of young-reader novels that chronicle the adventures of [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] between [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

==Publisher's summary==
<div align="center">'''Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker.'''<br />'''Master and apprentice.'''<br />'''Chosen by fate. Destined for conflict.'''</div>

''A Senator's son has vanished. A secret squad of renegade students exists in the shadows of his elite leadership school. Do they have something to do with the disappearance? Or is it linked to the Senator's unseen political foes, who are pushing the planet toward war?''

''The only way to solve the mystery and maintain peace is for two Jedi apprentices—Anakin Skywalker and his rival, Ferus Olin—to infiltrate one of the fiercest places in the galaxy: school.''

==Plot summary==
The [[Leadership School]] on [[Andara/Legends|Andara]] trains the next generation of the [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy’s]] privileged and elite beings to excel, but the sudden disappearance of one of its pupils – [[Gillam Tarturi]], son of an influential Senator – is cause for a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] probe. Two [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]]-[[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] teams, [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]], and [[Siri Tachi/Legends|Siri Tachi]] and [[Ferus Olin]], have been sent to Andara to [[Mission to Andara|investigate]] the disappearance of Gillam Tarturi, the son of the [[Berm Tarturi|Senator of Andara]]. It is believed that he was kidnapped to distract the [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] from the [[Politics/Legends|political]] problems in his home [[Andaran system|system]], possibly with the help of a young [[Squad/Legends|squad]] of [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] thought to be based at Andara's elite Leadership School&mdash;the same school Gillam disappeared from. Jedi undercover agents Anakin and Ferus enroll as transfer students at the school, Anakin supposedly on a scholarship and Ferus as the son of a high [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid-Rim]] official. Meanwhile, Obi-Wan and Siri investigate the ongoing Andaran system political struggle.

Gillam engineered his own disappearance as a vengeful strike against his [[Parent/Legends|father]]. Though the Jedi are able to scuttle this plot, Obi-Wan Kenobi is deeply disappointed in Anakin’s decision to support the mercenaries and his poor focus on the [[Jedi Code/Legends|Jedi Code]] throughout this mission.

==Continuity==
The supporting character of [[Reymet Autem]] first appeared in the ''[[Star Wars: Republic]]'' comic book story [[Star Wars: Republic: Honor and Duty|''Honor and Duty'']] (published in issues [[Republic 46|#46]]-[[Republic 48|48]], [[2002]]), which occurred later in the timeline. The [[Autem family]] story was more fully explored in comics books.<ref name="TERC" />

The novel misspelled [[Mas Amedda/Legends|Mas Amedda's]] name as "Mas Ameeda."

